<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><definitions xmlns="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL" xmlns:bpmndi="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/DI" xmlns:i18n="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/non-normative/extensions/i18n/1.0" xmlns:omgdc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DC" xmlns:omgdi="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DI" xmlns:signavio="http://www.signavio.com" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" exporter="Signavio Process Editor, http://www.signavio.com" exporterVersion="26.10.0-20260311103619+6e2d3ac" expressionLanguage="http://www.w3.org/TR/XPath" id="sid-9a4070a2-6c47-416c-9003-1e7a3ede3da6" targetNamespace="http://www.signavio.com" typeLanguage="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/2.0/20100501/BPMN20.xsd">
   <collaboration id="sid-8a5d66be-b98a-4e1b-b386-dff3d4f587a9">
      <extensionElements>
         <signavio:signavioDiagramMetaData metaKey="meta-processdescription" metaValue="  Manually  create a Requisition&#10;    Assign a vendor (supplier) to a requisition. MRP, inventory systems, and  other automatic feeds from system modules should have 'preferred' vendors  associated with items in the master files.   The option exists to assign vendors to manual requisitions at this  time, but it is not required. In the case of a third-party vendor, the vendor  can be identified or associated with the item in a master file. A contract or  scheduling agreement may be established for items from third party vendors,  to allow for easy reference of standard information on the requisition and  eventually on the purchase order.&#10;    Variants:&#10;    A.  Supplier is already established  on the master file and can be easily assigned to the requisition.&#10;    B. Supplier does not exist on the master file and additional sourcing work  may be required as well as an update to the vendor master file.&#10;    C. Supplier is tied to the item in a master file and carries forward  automatically.&#10;    Assign a vendor to a requisition.   Consider the requisition   'released' and convert it to a purchase order.&#10;    Variants:&#10;    - Individual release&#10;    - Collective release&#10;    Generate and distribute a report to those whose requisitions were either  changed or denied.  No notification is  required for those whose requisitions were approved without change.  They may query the system to check the  status when information is desired.&#10;     Variants:&#10;    A.  Communication for manual  requisitions can be handled by sending a report or message to the original requisitioner.&#10;    B. Communication for requisitions generated by the MRP or Inventory Systems  may require a central contact; but it  would be ideal if the ability to update other systems electronically  existed.&#10;    Note: As a next step, for selected list of vendors, buyers, material groups,  and multiple other attributes, the PO creation from PR can be scheduled as a  background job."/>
         <signavio:signavioDiagramMetaData metaKey="meta-approvedby" metaValue="[&quot;richard.w.taylor@intel.com&quot;]"/>
         <signavio:signavioDiagramMetaData metaKey="meta-approvalstatus" metaValue="ci1710756720720143051910"/>
         <signavio:signavioDiagramMetaData metaKey="meta-approvaldate" metaValue="16/04/24"/>
         <signavio:signavioDiagramMetaData metaKey="meta-approvalevidence" metaValue="[{&quot;label&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://intel.sharepoint.com/:u:/r/sites/inteldeloitteiao/Shared Documents/General/Implementation/06. PTP/3 Final Deliverables/1. Design/O. Process Approval Evidence/PM-070-020,070-040,070-080,080-090,080-150 Approval.msg?csf=1&amp;web=1&amp;e=mubUf2&quot;}]"/>
         <signavio:signavioDiagramMetaData metaKey="revisionid" metaValue="7b475dcc0caa4450bc70078fb621a89c"/>
